social_posts.post_text: Watching you grow over the past 4 months and seeing you learn more and more is the coolest experience for me as a new dad. You’re so happy and it’s definitely contagious 😆 I love you baby Olivia

(Get the chocolate version for more flavor and get chocolate chips to mix in too) it’s that time of the year! Make this easy treat with the fam this holiday!

They love each other 🥰❤️

This Christmas is going to be the best Christmas ever 🥰 Shania and I are excited to have our very first Christmas with our baby girl this year! Giving her lots of love and joy is what we will always have for our precious baby girl. I’m so excited to create magical memories with our little family and start new traditions ❤️

Made some fried chicken for the first time and it’s a lot easier than I expected! BUT I forgot to season my chicken! I didn’t forget to season my flour though so that’s good haha use the level up series that @smokinandgrillinwithab sells! (Definitely a level up) added in some of that Trader Joe’s biscuits and WOW they did not disappoint! Going back tomorrow for more!

Happy holidays and New Year from us! This will be the first holidays we spend as a family with many many more to come! So excited to start new family traditions and be happy about the holidays now! Olivia, I love you so much and I’m going to be the best dad I can be for you ❤️ Shania, I love you so much and I’m happy that you’re my baby mama ❤️ I wouldn’t want it any other way.

2022 was the best year of my life.. When Shania and I found out in November that we were pregnant, we didn’t really understand how real this was for the both of us. But one thing we did know was we couldn’t wait to love our little one. The experience of seeing Shania pregnant was beautiful. We couldn’t wait to meet Olivia. We expected to go in and have a natural birth but some things came up and had to do an emergency C section… I didn’t know what to expect as I was in shock for about 8 hours because what followed up after that was the hemorrhage… luckily Shania is such a strong woman and the hospital was on point to do what they had to in order to keep her healthy.. I’ll forever love you both. 2022 was a year of growth and love. I’m excited to capitalize on that in 2023 and buy a home for our family 🥰 I love you 😘

Today you’re officially 6 months old! Wow has time flies but also so many memories built within that time. Watching you grow/learn is the coolest thing to see as a new dad. We hope to continue to make you laugh and be happy my sweet baby girl ❤️
Had to take a moment today just to hold Olivia and have a quick dance. Idk why just felt like I needed to.

After a 3 year battle fighting brain cancer, one of the most amazing/influential women I’ve ever met has sadly passed away on January 24th 2023.. it’s taken me sometime to really process this news because of everything going on with moving to Las Vegas and many other things.. Liane was my mentor at the YMCA as well. She believed in me so much and has been so supportive for over 10 years. She worked so hard and not just for herself and family. But for us YMCA kids who she claimed to be a mom of. I proudly accepted that. The conversations we had prior to her passing was mainly how much I thanked her for believing in me for all these years. It’s still so hard to process this because I simply can’t believe it.. there isn’t enough words to truly describe how amazing and supportive Liane was.. I’ll forever cherish her. I wish she got to meet Olivia in person.. but I did make sure every other week to send lots of photos so she can see her. The first picture is the last time I saw Liane. At her house for a gathering knowing this day would come.. she was strong. I’ll miss you so much Liane and thank you again for everything you’ve done for me..
Happy Valentine’s Day to my two beautiful girls 🥰 you are the loves of my life and I’m so thankful to have both of you!

The absolute best part about being a new dad is finding these big key moments and milestones Olivia is making! The fact she is now holding herself of and just so happy is amazing. This is truly amazing and I’m so happy to be Olivia’s dad. I’ll always be sure you’re the happiest

My precious baby girl! Crazy how fast time has been going but also how many memories we’ve developed so far! I’ve been loving every single moment of fatherhood and making you smile 😊 I hope to continue to build you the life I didn’t get to have 🥰

Today you’re 8 months! Time is flying, but I’m enjoying every second of it with you ❤️ I love how much you smile and giggle. It truly warms my heart. When I feel down you bring me to cheer with just a smile. You make me so happy and I hope to continue to make you happier. I love you so much ❤️ -Dad

April 1st 1993 is when I was born. Yesterday marked 30 years of life..29 was a year of growth for me. My biggest core memories from my year at 29 was of course having Olivia.. this little girl means the world to me! Watching her grow and smile and cry just is so new to me. I’ve never had love like this before and I feel I’ve grown more as a man and a new father. Another core memory is Shania being the best/strongest mother to Olivia. Having to go through 10 months of being pregnant, 3 days of labor, emergency c-section, having to go down to the OR 2 hours after C section due to loss of LOTS of blood, to come back from all that and being an amazing human being/mother. I’m so happy for our lives, seeing each other grow into the people we want to become. Another thing this last year that was huge for me was my first car purchase ever. I bought a Tesla Model Y and even though it’s now way cheaper and you get a tax credit. I’m still happy with the car. Another core memory this year that I saved for last was income. At 29 I’ve made the most money ever and what a good year to make all of it! All for the family. Now that I turned 30 on April 1st, I hope to maximize everything this year as well as buy a home. Thank you everyone for your birthday wishes!
Grateful for our little family.

I’m happy I get to help you out when I can to give you a break. I love you honey 🥰

This baby is growing so fast! 9 months old and is just the cutest. I’m proud to be your dad and give you all the love you deserve! You’re my purpose to keep moving forward, to never give up and keep working hard to provide a life for you.

Happy Mothers Day to this amazing woman right here ❤️ you’ve been such a great Mom to Olivia, you do everything you can to make our little girl happy and it doesn’t go unnoticed. I see all the great you do for our little family and you’re much appreciated. I love you so much and I can’t wait to continue to grow with you 😍
Throw back to Olivia’s first time at #disneyland hope to bring her often to the happiest place on earth!

Once upon a time, I fell in love with you. Our story as it reaches the next chapter is only getting better. We have a beautiful daughter that you’ve went through tremendous lengths just to deliver. We have 2 funny dogs that are constantly making us laugh. Now we’re engaged. What a funny thing to say lol I feel like kids and being like “let’s play house and we’re married” lol 😂 you’ve been hinting and hinting and dropping all these hints on brilliant earth emails haha now the next question is when is the wedding… that will take further planning, but it will be well worth the wait. To forever my love 🥂

As I get older, I start to realize the importance of being present, happy and loving. The hard work I do pays off by seeing my little family smile. When I was Olivia’s age, my parents didn’t have this kind of lifestyle that I do now. Now they were young and it wasn’t easy. I’m thankful I can give Olivia the time she needs and the love she deserves. This post is dedicated to all the parents who are working their tail off for their families!

I want to start this post with gratitude. How grateful I am for good health. Not just for me, but my family. Olivia is 11 months as of June 17th and WOW. How crazy that less than a month and she will be 1! She’s hitting so many miles stones, from kinda walking to crawling upstairs and learning sign language. I’m so proud of Shania and I for doing our very best to raise this precious child. It has definitely been challenging for us in many ways, like moving our whole compound to Vegas where we don’t know what’s next. We’re getting over these obstacles and never giving up. My motivation is you Olivia. I’ll always provide for you. You’ll have a roof over your head, you won’t go hungry, you’ll grow strong, smart and happy. I love being your dad Olivia 😘

This Saturday I will be helping you understand the process of starting a video podcast! Looking forward to helping you get started! If you’re interested in coming send me a message saying IGNITE and for the first 10 people who message and confirm will get something! Link is in BIO but be sure to message me first! @sr.lasvegas

Happy 1st birthday Olivia! You are so loved and I’m so happy to be your dad. You’ve brought so much joy to my heart and I love you more and more each day! Now to Shania, even though today was Olivia’s birthday, this day is also dedicated to you. What we all went through in that hospital was very hard and I’m so thankful to have you in my life. I love you both 🔥❤️ we are parents and doing such a great job at it!

Her first steps.. wow. The amount of happiness I feel when Olivia reaches each of her milestones. I remember changing her diaper for the first time, swaddling her, always a bottle of milk on deck. Now just a growing girl growing fast in front of my eyes. I want to continue to take more photos and videos. She would love to look at all these and the ones we don’t post. Happy first steps baby! Many more to come :)

One of the best hacks to creating consistent content is to just be yourself! It’s tiring to always feel like you gotta bring your 100% energy. 

I’m not against bringing the heat but if you want to play the long game, BE YOU!

Men: stop counting down and just take a bunch LOL
(Obviously this was in a joking manner)
Cabo was beautiful

She’s grown up so fast, yet beautifully. Yes time does go by past, but we have so many amazing memories we can always look back on when we miss that newborn baby girl 👧 being a girl dad is amazing, it’s the best thing that’s ever happened to me.

Words can’t express how much I love being a dad. When we first knew that Shania was pregnant, in a weird way I felt prepared. Even though my whole life I said “I’ll wait till I’m financially free and successful and have a house.” But when the moment came to be a dad, I was ready, I felt prepared and proud. To give Olivia a life she will love. To be a dad it’s hard. There is so many  parents deal with a lot, especially in the first few years. But one thing that’s free, that you can give an unlimited amount of is love. So if you’re a new parent or  you already have kids, just remember how amazing you are to have that responsibility. Love the crap out of that kid. Smile at them, hold them, tell them how much you love them. They will remember that more than the material things. Olivia I love you so much and I’m so proud of the little lady you’re becoming. You’re my baby and I love you so much.
